@ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5117

### Register a user (returns access + refresh token)
# @name register
POST {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "sort-demo@test.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "displayName": "Sort Demo"
}

### Capture the access token from the register response above
@token = {{register.response.body.accessToken.token}}

### List transactions — default order (OccurredOn desc, no sort params)
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List transactions — sort by amount, descending (largest first)
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions?sortBy=amount&sortOrder=desc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List transactions — sort by amount, ascending (smallest first)
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions?sortBy=amount&sortOrder=asc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List transactions — sort by occurredOn ascending (oldest first)
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions?sortBy=occurredOn&sortOrder=asc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List transactions — sort by category name A→Z
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions?sortBy=categoryName&sortOrder=asc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List transactions — sort by note ascending (nulls first in PostgreSQL)
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions?sortBy=note&sortOrder=asc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List transactions — invalid sortBy should return 400 Bad Request
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions?sortBy=garbage
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List transactions — combine filter + sort (expense only, amount desc)
GET {{ExpenseTracker.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transactions?type=1&sortBy=amount&sortOrder=desc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
